# S2-5: Prisma Enum Refactoring - Walkthrough
 stone

I have implemented the content moderation flow, allowing users to report inappropriate content and admins to review and act on these reports.

## Changes Made

### Database Schema
- **Modified [User](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/UserProfilePage.jsx#6-129)**: Added `role` field (defaulting to `"USER"`).
- **Modified [Turn](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx#24-35)**: Added `isHidden` boolean field.
- **New Model [Report](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/components/ReportButton.jsx#4-92)**: Tracks reports against turns or logs (reporter token, reason, status).
- **New Model `ModerationAction`**: Records actions taken by moderators.

### Backend Implementation
- **Moderation Controller & Routes**:
    - `POST /api/reports`: Anonymous or authenticated users can flag content.
    - `GET /api/moderation/queue`: Admin-only access to pending reports.
    - `POST /api/moderation/action`: Admin-only capability to `HIDE_TURN`, `CLOSE_LOG`, or `DISMISS`.
- **[requireAdmin](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/middleware/auth.js#156-192) Middleware**: A robust guard that checks for either an `ADMIN` role in a JWT or a shared `X-Admin-Secret` header.
- **Turn Redaction**: Updated the logs controller to automatically replace the content of hidden turns with `[content removed]` for non-admin requests.

### Frontend Implementation
- **[ReportButton](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/components/ReportButton.jsx#4-92) Component**: A small, non-obtrusive component added to each turn and the log header.
- **[ModerationPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/ModerationPage.jsx#4-118)**: A dedicated admin dashboard accessible at `/moderation`. It uses an `ADMIN_SECRET` for authorization (stored in `localStorage` for convenience).
- **Updated [LogDetailPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx#36-303)**: Now displays the report buttons and reflects redacted content.

### S2-4: Screenshot Sharing Flow
- **Themed Export**: Users can now export completed logs as PNG images.
- **Themes**: Three themes are supported:
    - **Minimal**: Modern, white design.
    - **Nocturne**: Dark mode with high-contrast text.
    - **Parchment**: Classic aged paper look with serif fonts.
- **Technology**: Used `html-to-image` for client-side SVG-to-PNG rendering.
- **Branding**: Every exported image includes "Written collaboratively on Collective Unconscious" branding at the bottom.
- **Integration**: Added a "Share as Image" button to [LogDetailPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx#36-303) that only appears when a log is `COMPLETED`.

### S2-5: Prisma Enum Refactoring
- **Objective**: Improve data integrity by replacing raw string fields with formal Prisma `enum` types.
- **Enums Added**:
    - `LogStatus`: `ACTIVE`, `COMPLETED`
    - `Category`: `FREEWRITING`, `HAIKU`, `POEM`, `SHORT_NOVEL`
    - `AccessMode`: `OPEN`, `PRIVATE`
    - `TurnMode`: `FREESTYLE`, `STRUCTURED`
    - `UserRole`: `USER`, `ADMIN`
    - `ReportStatus`: `PENDING`, `DISMISSED`, `ACTIONED`
- **Backend**: Updated controllers and Zod schemas to use upper-case Enum variants. Fixes applied to [logs.js](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/controllers/logs.js) and [moderation.controller.js](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/controllers/moderation.controller.js).
- **Frontend**: Refactored [LanguageContext.jsx](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/context/LanguageContext.jsx) and [LogCard.jsx](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/components/LogCard.jsx) to dynamically map these Enums to localized strings, ensuring the UI remains user-friendly while the data layer is robust.

